# Secrets. The API key lives here. Never commit it.
# Copy .env.example to .env and put your own key in that.
.env

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Run artefacts
*.log
nohup.out

# Superseded. Everything in it is now in README.md, BUILD_LOG.md, or
# docs/SafePlate_Architecture.pdf, so it is only here to be confusing.
SafePlate_Explained.pdf


# Deliberately NOT ignored, in case you were wondering:
#
#   cache.json    The model's readings of the menu, and the second model's checks
#                 on those readings. This is committed on purpose. It is what lets
#                 the app run with no API key and no network, and it is what the
#                 test suite grades the model against. It holds menu labels and
#                 nothing else. There is no personal data in it.
#
#   .streamlit/   Config only. It switches Streamlit's usage telemetry off, which
#                 matters for a project that argues for data minimisation.
